FAKE PRODUCT IDENTIFICATION

Home Register Login

Counterfeit products have made consumers more resistant to buying goods online due to a lack of trust. In turn, authentic brands will be affected as they lose business. On the other hand, uninformed consumers will unintentionally help counterfeit brands gain profit while reducing profits and success of authentic brands. These issues have created an immense need for a reliable way to authenticate products before being bought, especially if they are being exchanged between consumers (second hand).

Today, blockchain technology provides a reliable solution to provide a platform of trust between consumers. By creating a distributed ledger with consensus, provenance, immutability, and finality, to allow consumers to ensure the authenticity of their products, sales of counterfeiting products will be significantly reduced while allowing consumers to shop without uncertainty.
